org.ow2.proactive.resourcemanager.core.recovery

Class FakeDownNodeForRecovery

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.ow2.proactive.resourcemanager.core.recovery.FakeDownNodeForRecovery
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Serializable, org.objectweb.proactive.core.node.Node

    public class FakeDownNodeForRecovery
extends Object
implements org.objectweb.proactive.core.node.Node, Serializable
    Almost empty implementation of the Node interface for the special case in which the resource manager recovery mechanism has to handle down nodes. Indeed, as down nodes are not reachable, it is impossible to retrieve more information than what has been saved in database for these nodes, specifically its name and URL. Note that we do not want to store Node information in database neither because most of it is not Serializable Nevertheless, even down nodes need to be recovered as fully instantiated Node because they are handled as this in lifecycle policies, in which mostly the node's URL is used to ensure proper handling.
